# Twilight Violet theme and dropdowns

## Theme name

The app theme is named **Twilight Violet**: dark backgrounds, light text, purple accent (primary buttons, focus rings, links). All UI must use design tokens from `src/styles/tokens.css`; no raw hex in components.

## Dropdowns (mandatory)

All dropdowns must use the **themed** custom component, not the computer-default native `<select>`.

- Use **`DropdownSelect`** from `@/components/ui` for every dropdown (contact Subject, editor LLM selector, settings, etc.).
- Do **not** use the native HTML `<select>` element in user-facing UI; it ignores our theme and looks like the OS default.
- The `Select` component (native `<select>` styled with tokens) only styles the trigger; the open list is browser-default. Prefer `DropdownSelect` for a fully themed open state (dark panel, purple hover/selected).

When adding new forms or settings that need a picker, use `DropdownSelect` with `options: SelectOption[]`, `value`, and `onChange`.
